com.samysadi.acs.user

Interface User

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Cloneable, Entity, Notifier, Probed
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    UserDefault

    public interface User
extends Entity
    A user is a simulation entity that utilizes Cloud resources.
    It owns a set of VMs and storage Files.

    1.0

    • Method Detail

      • clone

        User clone()
        Description copied from interface: Entity
        Creates a clone of this entity and sets its parent to null.

        This is a deep clone method which also clones almost all children entities and sets their parents to the newly created clone. The only children which are not cloned are those implementing the UncloneableEntity interface.

        Implementations must ensure that the new clone will be independent from the current entity.

        Specified by:
        clone in interface Entity
        Specified by:

      • getVirtualMachines

        List<VirtualMachine> getVirtualMachines()
        Returns a list of VirtualMachine that are owned by this user.

        The returned virtual machines are not actual children of this User entity, and the list is kept updated indirectly through listening to NotificationCodes.USER_VM_ATTACHED and NotificationCodes.USER_VM_DETACHED.

        The returned list should not include ThinClientVirtualMachines. Use getThinClients() to get ThinClients first if you want to list those.

        Returns:
        a list of VirtualMachine that are owned by this user

      • getStorageFiles

        List<StorageFile> getStorageFiles()
        Returns a list of files that are owned by this user.

        The returned files are not actual children of this User entity, and the list is kept updated indirectly through listening to NotificationCodes.USER_STORAGEFILE_ATTACHED and NotificationCodes.USER_STORAGEFILE_DETACHED.

        Returns:
        a list of files that are owned by this user
